-- UK watchdog to probe PwC over Tesco accounting scandal
-- By Neil Maidment
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 05:26AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 22 (Reuters) - Britain's accounting watchdog, the Financial Reporting Council (FRC), said on Monday it had launched an inquiry into PwC [PWC.UL] over its auditing of Tesco's <TSCO.L> 2012, 2013 and 2014 accounts.

In October Tesco, Britain's biggest retailer, said it had misstated its profits by 263 million pounds ($411 million), compounding a disastrous run of profit warnings. [ID:nL6N0SI14H] PwC were not immediately available for comment. The watchdog has powers to sanction accounting firms and their staff for failing to apply book-keeping rules properly.